# cms/.gitignore — gitignore rules for the CMS content-production
# sub-tree. Anything that's specifically about the content runtime /
# CMS pipeline state lives here; cross-project concerns (Python
# __pycache__, IDE dirs, OS junk, secrets, ...) stay in the root
# .gitignore so they apply uniformly.

# CMS-host secrets — never commit. Created by env.sh init from
# cms/.env.example.cms. Resolved by lib.sh::resolve_content_env_file.
.env

# CMS working dir — generated TTS MP3s and any future per-machine
# state (logs, caches, ...) that content.sh / generate_audio.py writes.
# Lives inside the project (cms/.local/) so default-path writes
# work on Windows + sandboxed Linux hosts without extra setup. dev/prod
# runtime does NOT read this — audio is uploaded to Tencent Cloud COS
# by generate_audio.py (configured via CLOUD_* env vars). The db image
# itself no longer carries audio files.
.local/